<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Assembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Make sure the connecting rod and piston are assembled correctly to avoid engine damage. The large
                    chamfer side of the connecting rod must be located next to the crankshaft fillet.
                </para>
                <para>Make sure the lock slots and forging feature on the connecting rod are opposite the "cam" marking
                    found on the piston head.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200736" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Proper Assembly of the Piston and Connecting Rod</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Stamped "Cam," Part Number, (Service Pistons Include Oversize
                    Designation)
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Large Chamfer Side of Connecting Rod</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the piston to the connecting rod as follows:</para>
            <figure id="f1200737" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2588.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing the Piston Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Pin</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Rings</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the piston pin bore in the connecting rod, the piston bore and the piston pin
                    with clean engine oil.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1200738" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2587.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
                    <caption>Installing the Piston Pin Retaining Ring</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Pliers</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Ring</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The retaining ring has a smooth finish side and a rough finish side. The smooth finish
                            side faces the piston pin.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use pliers to install a piston pin retaining ring at one end of the piston pin bore.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert the connecting rod into the piston. Make sure the bored holes of the connecting
                    rod and piston are aligned.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Slide the piston pin through the bored holes, stopping at the previously installed
                    retaining ring.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the second retaining ring.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200739" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing Rings Onto Piston</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring Expansion Tool</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the piston ring expansion tool to install the oil control ring into the bottom piston
                groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The intermediate ring is identified by the two "OO" marks located on the top surface of the ring.
                    Make sure the ring is installed with the identifications marks facing up.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200740" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1906.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Intermediate Piston Ring Identification Mark</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Ring Gap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Identification Mark ("OO")</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the piston ring expansion tool to install the intermediate ring into the middle piston
                groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The compression ring is identified by one single "O" mark located on the top surface of the ring.
                    Make sure the ring is installed with the identification mark facing up.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200741" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1907.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Top Piston Ring Identification Mark</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Ring Gap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Identification Mark ("O")</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the piston ring expansion tool to install the compression ring into the top piston
                groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
